  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, I noticed how you explained your app idea using a cricket analogy — that was clear and smart! How did the team meeting go?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "We pitched the idea, and the team liked it. I used a simple example — like how a bowler plans before delivering — to explain our approach. Phew, that meeting was long! 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That was a good example — bowlers do plan carefully! I get that the meeting was long. What's next for the project?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Now we need to build a prototype. The team wants to test the core idea first, like a trial match before the real game. I’ll probably spend the next week coding."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds like a smart plan. A trial match is always helpful. Do you enjoy working on prototypes, or do you prefer the final build?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, I like both but prototyping is more fun, like batting first in a tight match. You have freedom to experiment. But the final build is satisfying too — like taking a key wicket. Balance, right? 😄"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get what you mean — batting first is exciting! You said \"prototyping is more fun\" — and that's correct. I like how you explained it. Do you usually work on similar projects?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Mostly yes. I work on fintech apps, but this project is a bit different — more creative. It feels like a startup vibe. You know, like watching a new Bollywood movie — unexpected but interesting!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that — startups do feel fresh and risky! You said \"more creative\" and \"unexpected but interesting\" — great flow! Have you seen any good Bollywood movies lately?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I watched *Dil Bechara* recently — it’s based on a Hollywood movie but the emotions are so raw. The lead actor is great, but the music... *naachey waley gane* are stuck in my head! What about you? Any good movies you’ve seen?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get it — good music stays with you! You said \"the emotions are so raw\" — that's perfect. I enjoyed *Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara* — fun and full of energy. What's your favourite Bollywood movie?"
    }
  ],
